<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="78" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1562,1731]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,289,1598,1623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">Biology</emphasis>
: the new species has been collected in emergence traps in a calcareous tufa barrier, where it co-occurs with 
<taxonomicName authority="Krek" authorityName="Krek" authorityYear="1972" box="[207,568,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Pericoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudocalcilega">
<emphasis box="[207,505,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">Pericoma pseudocalcilega</emphasis>
Krek
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="EatOn." authorityName="EatOn." box="[623,830,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Pericoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blandula">
<emphasis box="[623,750,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">P. blandula</emphasis>
Eaton.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="78" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1562,1731]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1670,1695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="78">Etymology</emphasis>
: the species is named after Miljenko Ivković for his immense help in constructing the emergence traps and his constant help and always positive attitude in the field from the start of the project.
</paragraph>
